61// === SpeculativeJIT ===
62//
63// The SpeculativeJIT is used to generate a fast, but potentially
64// incomplete code path for the dataflow. When code generating
65// we may make assumptions about operand types, dynamically check,
66// and bail-out to an alternate code path if these checks fail.
67// Importantly, the speculative code path cannot be reentered once
68// a speculative check has failed. This allows the SpeculativeJIT
69// to propagate type information (including information that has
70// only speculatively been asserted) through the dataflow.
71DECLARE_ALLOCATOR_WITH_HEAP_IDENTIFIER(SpeculativeJIT);
72class SpeculativeJIT {
73 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED_WITH_HEAP_IDENTIFIER(SpeculativeJIT);
74 friend struct OSRExit;
75private:
76 typedef JITCompiler::TrustedImm32 TrustedImm32;
77 typedef JITCompiler::Imm32 Imm32;
78 typedef JITCompiler::ImmPtr ImmPtr;
79 typedef JITCompiler::TrustedImm64 TrustedImm64;
80 typedef JITCompiler::Imm64 Imm64;
81
82 // These constants are used to set priorities for spill order for
83 // the register allocator.
84#if USE(JSVALUE64)
85 enum SpillOrder {
86 SpillOrderConstant = 1, // no spill, and cheap fill
87 SpillOrderSpilled = 2, // no spill
88 SpillOrderJS = 4, // needs spill
89 SpillOrderCell = 4, // needs spill
90 SpillOrderStorage = 4, // needs spill
91 SpillOrderInteger = 5, // needs spill and box
92 SpillOrderBoolean = 5, // needs spill and box
93 SpillOrderDouble = 6, // needs spill and convert
94 };
95#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
96 enum SpillOrder {
97 SpillOrderConstant = 1, // no spill, and cheap fill
98 SpillOrderSpilled = 2, // no spill
99 SpillOrderJS = 4, // needs spill
100 SpillOrderStorage = 4, // needs spill
101 SpillOrderDouble = 4, // needs spill
102 SpillOrderInteger = 5, // needs spill and box
103 SpillOrderCell = 5, // needs spill and box
104 SpillOrderBoolean = 5, // needs spill and box
105 };
106#endif
107
108 enum UseChildrenMode { CallUseChildren, UseChildrenCalledExplicitly };
109

119 struct TrustedImmPtr {
120 template <typename T>
121 explicit TrustedImmPtr(T* value)
122 : m_value(value)
123 {
124 static_assert(!std::is_base_of<JSCell, T>::value, "To use a GC pointer, the graph must be aware of it. Use SpeculativeJIT::TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer instead.");
125 }
126
127 explicit TrustedImmPtr(RegisteredStructure structure)
128 : m_value(structure.get())
129 { }
130
131 explicit TrustedImmPtr(std::nullptr_t)
132 : m_value(nullptr)
133 { }
134
135 explicit TrustedImmPtr(FrozenValue* value)
136 : m_value(value->cell())
137 {
138 RELEASE_ASSERT(value->value().isCell());
139 }
140
141 explicit TrustedImmPtr(size_t value)
142 : m_value(bitwise_cast<void*>(value))
143 {
144 }
145
146 static TrustedImmPtr weakPointer(Graph& graph, JSCell* cell)
147 {
148 graph.m_plan.weakReferences().addLazily(cell);
149 return TrustedImmPtr(bitwise_cast<size_t>(cell));
150 }
151
152 operator MacroAssembler::TrustedImmPtr() const { return m_value; }
153 operator MacroAssembler::TrustedImm() const { return m_value; }
154
155 intptr_t asIntptr()
156 {
157 return m_value.asIntptr();
158 }
159
160 private:
161 MacroAssembler::TrustedImmPtr m_value;
162 };

169 BasicBlock* nextBlock()
170 {
171 for (BlockIndex resultIndex = m_block->index + 1; ; resultIndex++) {
172 if (resultIndex >= m_jit.graph().numBlocks())
173 return nullptr;
174 if (BasicBlock* result = m_jit.graph().block(resultIndex))
175 return result;
176 }
177 }

204 // Used to check whether a child node is on its last use,
205 // and its machine registers may be reused.
206 bool canReuse(Node* node)
207 {
208 return generationInfo(node).useCount() == 1;
209 }
210 bool canReuse(Node* nodeA, Node* nodeB)
211 {
212 return nodeA == nodeB && generationInfo(nodeA).useCount() == 2;
213 }
214 bool canReuse(Edge nodeUse)
215 {
216 return canReuse(nodeUse.node());
217 }
218 GPRReg reuse(GPRReg reg)
219 {
220 m_gprs.lock(reg);
221 return reg;
222 }
223 FPRReg reuse(FPRReg reg)
224 {
225 m_fprs.lock(reg);
226 return reg;
227 }

229 // Allocate a gpr/fpr.
230 GPRReg allocate()
231 {
232#if ENABLE(DFG_REGISTER_ALLOCATION_VALIDATION)
233 m_jit.addRegisterAllocationAtOffset(m_jit.debugOffset());
234#endif
235 VirtualRegister spillMe;
236 GPRReg gpr = m_gprs.allocate(spillMe);
237 if (spillMe.isValid()) {
238#if USE(JSVALUE32_64)
239 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(spillMe);
240 if ((info.registerFormat() & DataFormatJS))
241 m_gprs.release(info.tagGPR() == gpr ? info.payloadGPR() : info.tagGPR());
242#endif
243 spill(spillMe);
244 }
245 return gpr;
246 }
247 GPRReg allocate(GPRReg specific)
248 {
249#if ENABLE(DFG_REGISTER_ALLOCATION_VALIDATION)
250 m_jit.addRegisterAllocationAtOffset(m_jit.debugOffset());
251#endif
252 VirtualRegister spillMe = m_gprs.allocateSpecific(specific);
253 if (spillMe.isValid()) {
254#if USE(JSVALUE32_64)
255 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(spillMe);
256 RELEASE_ASSERT(info.registerFormat() != DataFormatJSDouble);
257 if ((info.registerFormat() & DataFormatJS))
258 m_gprs.release(info.tagGPR() == specific ? info.payloadGPR() : info.tagGPR());
259#endif
260 spill(spillMe);
261 }
262 return specific;
263 }
264 GPRReg tryAllocate()
265 {
266 return m_gprs.tryAllocate();
267 }
268 FPRReg fprAllocate()
269 {
270#if ENABLE(DFG_REGISTER_ALLOCATION_VALIDATION)
271 m_jit.addRegisterAllocationAtOffset(m_jit.debugOffset());
272#endif
273 VirtualRegister spillMe;
274 FPRReg fpr = m_fprs.allocate(spillMe);
275 if (spillMe.isValid())
276 spill(spillMe);
277 return fpr;
278 }

280 // Check whether a VirtualRegsiter is currently in a machine register.
281 // We use this when filling operands to fill those that are already in
282 // machine registers first (by locking VirtualRegsiters that are already
283 // in machine register before filling those that are not we attempt to
284 // avoid spilling values we will need immediately).
285 bool isFilled(Node* node)
286 {
287 return generationInfo(node).registerFormat() != DataFormatNone;
288 }
289 bool isFilledDouble(Node* node)
290 {
291 return generationInfo(node).registerFormat() == DataFormatDouble;
292 }
293
294 // Called on an operand once it has been consumed by a parent node.
295 void use(Node* node)
296 {
297 if (!node->hasResult())
298 return;
299 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfo(node);
300
301 // use() returns true when the value becomes dead, and any
302 // associated resources may be freed.
303 if (!info.use(*m_stream))
304 return;
305
306 // Release the associated machine registers.
307 DataFormat registerFormat = info.registerFormat();
308#if USE(JSVALUE64)
309 if (registerFormat == DataFormatDouble)
310 m_fprs.release(info.fpr());
311 else if (registerFormat != DataFormatNone)
312 m_gprs.release(info.gpr());
313#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
314 if (registerFormat == DataFormatDouble)
315 m_fprs.release(info.fpr());
316 else if (registerFormat & DataFormatJS) {
317 m_gprs.release(info.tagGPR());
318 m_gprs.release(info.payloadGPR());
319 } else if (registerFormat != DataFormatNone)
320 m_gprs.release(info.gpr());
321#endif
322 }
323 void use(Edge nodeUse)
324 {
325 use(nodeUse.node());
326 }

367 // These methods are used when generating 'unexpected'
368 // calls out from JIT code to C++ helper routines -
369 // they spill all live values to the appropriate
370 // slots in the JSStack without changing any state
371 // in the GenerationInfo.
372 SilentRegisterSavePlan silentSavePlanForGPR(VirtualRegister spillMe, GPRReg source);
373 SilentRegisterSavePlan silentSavePlanForFPR(VirtualRegister spillMe, FPRReg source);
374 void silentSpill(const SilentRegisterSavePlan&);
375 void silentFill(const SilentRegisterSavePlan&);
376
377 template<typename CollectionType>
378 void silentSpill(const CollectionType& savePlans)
379 {
380 for (unsigned i = 0; i < savePlans.size(); ++i)
381 silentSpill(savePlans[i]);
382 }
383
384 template<typename CollectionType>
385 void silentFill(const CollectionType& savePlans)
386 {
387 for (unsigned i = savePlans.size(); i--;)
388 silentFill(savePlans[i]);
389 }
390
391 template<typename CollectionType>
392 void silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(bool doSpill, CollectionType& plans, GPRReg exclude, GPRReg exclude2 = InvalidGPRReg, FPRReg fprExclude = InvalidFPRReg)
393 {
394 ASSERT(plans.isEmpty());
395 for (gpr_iterator iter = m_gprs.begin(); iter != m_gprs.end(); ++iter) {
396 GPRReg gpr = iter.regID();
397 if (iter.name().isValid() && gpr != exclude && gpr != exclude2) {
398 SilentRegisterSavePlan plan = silentSavePlanForGPR(iter.name(), gpr);
399 if (doSpill)
400 silentSpill(plan);
401 plans.append(plan);
402 }
403 }
404 for (fpr_iterator iter = m_fprs.begin(); iter != m_fprs.end(); ++iter) {
405 if (iter.name().isValid() && iter.regID() != fprExclude) {
406 SilentRegisterSavePlan plan = silentSavePlanForFPR(iter.name(), iter.regID());
407 if (doSpill)
408 silentSpill(plan);
409 plans.append(plan);
410 }
411 }
412 }
413 template<typename CollectionType>
414 void silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(bool doSpill, CollectionType& plans, NoResultTag)
415 {
416 silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(doSpill, plans, InvalidGPRReg, InvalidGPRReg, InvalidFPRReg);
417 }
418 template<typename CollectionType>
419 void silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(bool doSpill, CollectionType& plans, FPRReg exclude)
420 {
421 silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(doSpill, plans, InvalidGPRReg, InvalidGPRReg, exclude);
422 }
423 template<typename CollectionType>
424 void silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(bool doSpill, CollectionType& plans, JSValueRegs exclude)
425 {
426#if USE(JSVALUE32_64)
427 silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(doSpill, plans, exclude.tagGPR(), exclude.payloadGPR());
428#else
429 silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(doSpill, plans, exclude.gpr());
430#endif
431 }
432
433 void silentSpillAllRegisters(GPRReg exclude, GPRReg exclude2 = InvalidGPRReg, FPRReg fprExclude = InvalidFPRReg)
434 {
435 silentSpillAllRegistersImpl(true, m_plans, exclude, exclude2, fprExclude);
436 }
437 void silentSpillAllRegisters(FPRReg exclude)
438 {
439 silentSpillAllRegisters(InvalidGPRReg, InvalidGPRReg, exclude);
440 }
441 void silentSpillAllRegisters(JSValueRegs exclude)
442 {
443#if USE(JSVALUE64)
444 silentSpillAllRegisters(exclude.payloadGPR());
445#else
446 silentSpillAllRegisters(exclude.payloadGPR(), exclude.tagGPR());
447#endif
448 }
449
450 void silentFillAllRegisters()
451 {
452 while (!m_plans.isEmpty()) {
453 SilentRegisterSavePlan& plan = m_plans.last();
454 silentFill(plan);
455 m_plans.removeLast();
456 }
457 }

490 // Spill a VirtualRegister to the JSStack.
491 void spill(VirtualRegister spillMe)
492 {
493 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(spillMe);
494
495#if USE(JSVALUE32_64)
496 if (info.registerFormat() == DataFormatNone) // it has been spilled. JS values which have two GPRs can reach here
497 return;
498#endif
499 // Check the GenerationInfo to see if this value need writing
500 // to the JSStack - if not, mark it as spilled & return.
501 if (!info.needsSpill()) {
502 info.setSpilled(*m_stream, spillMe);
503 return;
504 }
505
506 DataFormat spillFormat = info.registerFormat();
507 switch (spillFormat) {
508 case DataFormatStorage: {
509 // This is special, since it's not a JS value - as in it's not visible to JS
510 // code.
511 m_jit.storePtr(info.gpr(), JITCompiler::addressFor(spillMe));
512 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, DataFormatStorage);
513 return;
514 }
515
516 case DataFormatInt32: {
517 m_jit.store32(info.gpr(), JITCompiler::payloadFor(spillMe));
518 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, DataFormatInt32);
519 return;
520 }
521
522#if USE(JSVALUE64)
523 case DataFormatDouble: {
524 m_jit.storeDouble(info.fpr(), JITCompiler::addressFor(spillMe));
525 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, DataFormatDouble);
526 return;
527 }
528
529 case DataFormatInt52:
530 case DataFormatStrictInt52: {
531 m_jit.store64(info.gpr(), JITCompiler::addressFor(spillMe));
532 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, spillFormat);
533 return;
534 }
535
536 default:
537 // The following code handles JSValues, int32s, and cells.
538 RELEASE_ASSERT(spillFormat == DataFormatCell || spillFormat & DataFormatJS);
539
540 GPRReg reg = info.gpr();
541 // We need to box int32 and cell values ...
542 // but on JSVALUE64 boxing a cell is a no-op!
543 if (spillFormat == DataFormatInt32)
544 m_jit.or64(GPRInfo::numberTagRegister, reg);
545
546 // Spill the value, and record it as spilled in its boxed form.
547 m_jit.store64(reg, JITCompiler::addressFor(spillMe));
548 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, (DataFormat)(spillFormat | DataFormatJS));
549 return;
550#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
551 case DataFormatCell:
552 case DataFormatBoolean: {
553 m_jit.store32(info.gpr(), JITCompiler::payloadFor(spillMe));
554 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, spillFormat);
555 return;
556 }
557
558 case DataFormatDouble: {
559 // On JSVALUE32_64 boxing a double is a no-op.
560 m_jit.storeDouble(info.fpr(), JITCompiler::addressFor(spillMe));
561 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, DataFormatDouble);
562 return;
563 }
564
565 default:
566 // The following code handles JSValues.
567 RELEASE_ASSERT(spillFormat & DataFormatJS);
568 m_jit.store32(info.tagGPR(), JITCompiler::tagFor(spillMe));
569 m_jit.store32(info.payloadGPR(), JITCompiler::payloadFor(spillMe));
570 info.spill(*m_stream, spillMe, spillFormat);
571 return;
572#endif
573 }
574 }

591 // Spill all VirtualRegisters back to the JSStack.
592 void flushRegisters()
593 {
594 for (gpr_iterator iter = m_gprs.begin(); iter != m_gprs.end(); ++iter) {
595 if (iter.name().isValid()) {
596 spill(iter.name());
597 iter.release();
598 }
599 }
600 for (fpr_iterator iter = m_fprs.begin(); iter != m_fprs.end(); ++iter) {
601 if (iter.name().isValid()) {
602 spill(iter.name());
603 iter.release();
604 }
605 }
606 }
607
608 // Used to ASSERT flushRegisters() has been called prior to
609 // calling out from JIT code to a C helper function.
610 bool isFlushed()
611 {
612 for (gpr_iterator iter = m_gprs.begin(); iter != m_gprs.end(); ++iter) {
613 if (iter.name().isValid())
614 return false;
615 }
616 for (fpr_iterator iter = m_fprs.begin(); iter != m_fprs.end(); ++iter) {
617 if (iter.name().isValid())
618 return false;
619 }
620 return true;
621 }

630 // Helper functions to enable code sharing in implementations of bit/shift ops.
631 void bitOp(NodeType op, int32_t imm, GPRReg op1, GPRReg result)
632 {
633 switch (op) {
634 case ArithBitAnd:
635 m_jit.and32(Imm32(imm), op1, result);
636 break;
637 case ArithBitOr:
638 m_jit.or32(Imm32(imm), op1, result);
639 break;
640 case ArithBitXor:
641 m_jit.xor32(Imm32(imm), op1, result);
642 break;
643 default:
644 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
645 }
646 }
647 void bitOp(NodeType op, GPRReg op1, GPRReg op2, GPRReg result)
648 {
649 switch (op) {
650 case ArithBitAnd:
651 m_jit.and32(op1, op2, result);
652 break;
653 case ArithBitOr:
654 m_jit.or32(op1, op2, result);
655 break;
656 case ArithBitXor:
657 m_jit.xor32(op1, op2, result);
658 break;
659 default:
660 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
661 }
662 }
663 void shiftOp(NodeType op, GPRReg op1, int32_t shiftAmount, GPRReg result)
664 {
665 switch (op) {
666 case ArithBitRShift:
667 m_jit.rshift32(op1, Imm32(shiftAmount), result);
668 break;
669 case ArithBitLShift:
670 m_jit.lshift32(op1, Imm32(shiftAmount), result);
671 break;
672 case BitURShift:
673 m_jit.urshift32(op1, Imm32(shiftAmount), result);
674 break;
675 default:
676 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
677 }
678 }
679 void shiftOp(NodeType op, GPRReg op1, GPRReg shiftAmount, GPRReg result)
680 {
681 switch (op) {
682 case ArithBitRShift:
683 m_jit.rshift32(op1, shiftAmount, result);
684 break;
685 case ArithBitLShift:
686 m_jit.lshift32(op1, shiftAmount, result);
687 break;
688 case BitURShift:
689 m_jit.urshift32(op1, shiftAmount, result);
690 break;
691 default:
692 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
693 }
694 }

696 // Returns the index of the branch node if peephole is okay, UINT_MAX otherwise.
697 unsigned detectPeepHoleBranch()
698 {
699 // Check that no intervening nodes will be generated.
700 for (unsigned index = m_indexInBlock + 1; index < m_block->size() - 1; ++index) {
701 Node* node = m_block->at(index);
702 if (!node->shouldGenerate())
703 continue;
704 // Check if it's a Phantom that can be safely ignored.
705 if (node->op() == Phantom && !node->child1())
706 continue;
707 return UINT_MAX;
708 }
709
710 // Check if the lastNode is a branch on this node.
711 Node* lastNode = m_block->terminal();
712 return lastNode->op() == Branch && lastNode->child1() == m_currentNode ? m_block->size() - 1 : UINT_MAX;
713 }

770 // Called once a node has completed code generation but prior to setting
771 // its result, to free up its children. (This must happen prior to setting
772 // the nodes result, since the node may have the same VirtualRegister as
773 // a child, and as such will use the same GeneratioInfo).
774 void useChildren(Node*);
775
776 // These method called to initialize the GenerationInfo
777 // to describe the result of an operation.
778 void strictInt32Result(GPRReg reg, Node* node, DataFormat format = DataFormatInt32, UseChildrenMode mode = CallUseChildren)
779 {
780 if (mode == CallUseChildren)
781 useChildren(node);
782
783 VirtualRegister virtualRegister = node->virtualRegister();
784 GenerationInfo& info = generationInfoFromVirtualRegister(virtualRegister);
785
786 if (format == DataFormatInt32) {
787 m_jit.jitAssertIsInt32(reg);
788 m_gprs.retain(reg, virtualRegister, SpillOrderInteger);
789 info.initInt32(node, node->refCount(), reg);
790 } else {
791#if USE(JSVALUE64)
792 RELEASE_ASSERT(format == DataFormatJSInt32);
793 m_jit.jitAssertIsJSInt32(reg);
794 m_gprs.retain(reg, virtualRegister, SpillOrderJS);
795 info.initJSValue(node, node->refCount(), reg, format);
796#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
797 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
798#endif
799 }
800 }
801 void strictInt32Result(GPRReg reg, Node* node, UseChildrenMode mode)
802 {
803 strictInt32Result(reg, node, DataFormatInt32, mode);
804 }

813 m_gprs.retain(reg, virtualRegister, SpillOrderJS);
814 info.initInt52(node, node->refCount(), reg, format);
815 }

974 JITCompiler::Call callOperationWithCallFrameRollbackOnException(V_JITOperation_Cb operation, CodeBlock* codeBlock)
975 {
976 // Do not register CodeBlock* as a weak-pointer.
977 m_jit.setupArguments<V_JITOperation_Cb>(TrustedImmPtr(static_cast<void*>(codeBlock)));
978 return appendCallWithCallFrameRollbackOnException(operation);
979 }

981 JITCompiler::Call callOperationWithCallFrameRollbackOnException(Z_JITOperation_G operation, GPRReg result, JSGlobalObject* globalObject)
982 {
983 m_jit.setupArguments<Z_JITOperation_G>(TrustedImmPtr::weakPointer(m_graph, globalObject));
984 return appendCallWithCallFrameRollbackOnExceptionSetResult(operation, result);

986
987 void prepareForExternalCall()
988 {
989#if !defined(NDEBUG) && !CPU(ARM_THUMB2) && !CPU(MIPS)
990 // We're about to call out to a "native" helper function. The helper
991 // function is expected to set topCallFrame itself with the CallFrame
992 // that is passed to it.
993 //
994 // We explicitly trash topCallFrame here so that we'll know if some of
995 // the helper functions are not setting topCallFrame when they should
996 // be doing so. Note: the previous value in topcallFrame was not valid
997 // anyway since it was not being updated by JIT'ed code by design.
998
999 for (unsigned i = 0; i < sizeof(void*) / 4; i++)
1000 m_jit.store32(TrustedImm32(0xbadbeef), reinterpret_cast<char*>(&vm().topCallFrame) + i * 4);
1001#endif
1002 m_jit.prepareCallOperation(vm());
1003 }
1004
1005 // These methods add call instructions, optionally setting results, and optionally rolling back the call frame on an exception.
1006 JITCompiler::Call appendCall(const FunctionPtr<CFunctionPtrTag> function)
1007 {
1008 prepareForExternalCall();
1009 m_jit.emitStoreCodeOrigin(m_currentNode->origin.semantic);
1010 return m_jit.appendCall(function);
1011 }
1012
1013 void appendCall(CCallHelpers::Address address)
1014 {
1015 prepareForExternalCall();
1016 m_jit.emitStoreCodeOrigin(m_currentNode->origin.semantic);
1017 m_jit.appendCall(address);
1018 }
1019
1020 JITCompiler::Call appendOperationCall(const FunctionPtr<OperationPtrTag> function)
1021 {
1022 prepareForExternalCall();
1023 m_jit.emitStoreCodeOrigin(m_currentNode->origin.semantic);
1024 return m_jit.appendOperationCall(function);
1025 }

1027 JITCompiler::Call appendCallWithCallFrameRollbackOnException(const FunctionPtr<CFunctionPtrTag> function)
1028 {
1029 JITCompiler::Call call = appendCall(function);
1030 m_jit.exceptionCheckWithCallFrameRollback();
1031 return call;
1032 }
1033
1034 JITCompiler::Call appendCallWithCallFrameRollbackOnExceptionSetResult(const FunctionPtr<CFunctionPtrTag> function, GPRReg result)
1035 {
1036 JITCompiler::Call call = appendCallWithCallFrameRollbackOnException(function);
1037 if ((result != InvalidGPRReg) && (result != GPRInfo::returnValueGPR))
1038 m_jit.move(GPRInfo::returnValueGPR, result);
1039 return call;
1040 }

1183 enum FallThroughMode {
1184 AtFallThroughPoint,
1185 ForceJump
1186 };
1187 void jump(BasicBlock* destination, FallThroughMode fallThroughMode = AtFallThroughPoint)
1188 {
1189 if (destination == nextBlock()
1190 && fallThroughMode == AtFallThroughPoint)
1191 return;
1192 addBranch(m_jit.jump(), destination);
1193 }

1197 m_branches.append(BranchRecord(jump, destination));

1258 struct StringSwitchCase {
1259 StringSwitchCase() { }
1260
1261 StringSwitchCase(StringImpl* string, BasicBlock* target)
1262 : string(string)
1263 , target(target)
1264 {
1265 }
1266
1267 bool operator<(const StringSwitchCase& other) const
1268 {
1269 return stringLessThan(*string, *other.string);
1270 }
1271

1831 Vector<SlowPathLambda> m_slowPathLambdas;
1832 Vector<SilentRegisterSavePlan> m_plans;
1833 std::optional<unsigned> m_outOfLineStreamIndex;
1834};

1836
1837// === Operand types ===
1838//
1839// These classes are used to lock the operands to a node into machine
1840// registers. These classes implement of pattern of locking a value
1841// into register at the point of construction only if it is already in
1842// registers, and otherwise loading it lazily at the point it is first
1843// used. We do so in order to attempt to avoid spilling one operand
1844// in order to make space available for another.
1845
1846class JSValueOperand {
1847 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
1848public:
1849 explicit JSValueOperand(SpeculativeJIT* jit, Edge edge, OperandSpeculationMode mode = AutomaticOperandSpeculation)
1850 : m_jit(jit)
1851 , m_edge(edge)
1852#if USE(JSVALUE64)
1853 , m_gprOrInvalid(InvalidGPRReg)
1854#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
1855 , m_isDouble(false)
1856#endif
1857 {
1858 ASSERT(m_jit);
1859 if (!edge)
1860 return;
1861 ASSERT_UNUSED(mode, mode == ManualOperandSpeculation || edge.useKind() == UntypedUse);
1862#if USE(JSVALUE64)
1863 if (jit->isFilled(node()))
1864 gpr();
1865#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
1866 m_register.pair.tagGPR = InvalidGPRReg;
1867 m_register.pair.payloadGPR = InvalidGPRReg;
1868 if (jit->isFilled(node()))
1869 fill();
1870#endif
1871 }
1872
1873 explicit JSValueOperand(JSValueOperand&& other)
1874 : m_jit(other.m_jit)
1875 , m_edge(other.m_edge)
1876 {
1877#if USE(JSVALUE64)
1878 m_gprOrInvalid = other.m_gprOrInvalid;
1879#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
1880 m_register.pair.tagGPR = InvalidGPRReg;
1881 m_register.pair.payloadGPR = InvalidGPRReg;
1882 m_isDouble = other.m_isDouble;
1883
1884 if (m_edge) {
1885 if (m_isDouble)
1886 m_register.fpr = other.m_register.fpr;
1887 else
1888 m_register.pair = other.m_register.pair;
1889 }
1890#endif
1891 other.m_edge = Edge();
1892#if USE(JSVALUE64)
1893 other.m_gprOrInvalid = InvalidGPRReg;
1894#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
1895 other.m_isDouble = false;
1896#endif
1897 }
1898
1899 ~JSValueOperand()
1900 {
1901 if (!m_edge)
1902 return;
1903#if USE(JSVALUE64)
1904 ASSERT(m_gprOrInvalid != InvalidGPRReg);
1905 m_jit->unlock(m_gprOrInvalid);
1906#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
1907 if (m_isDouble) {
1908 ASSERT(m_register.fpr != InvalidFPRReg);
1909 m_jit->unlock(m_register.fpr);
1910 } else {
1911 ASSERT(m_register.pair.tagGPR != InvalidGPRReg && m_register.pair.payloadGPR != InvalidGPRReg);
1912 m_jit->unlock(m_register.pair.tagGPR);
1913 m_jit->unlock(m_register.pair.payloadGPR);
1914 }
1915#endif
1916 }
1917
1918 Edge edge() const
1919 {
1920 return m_edge;
1921 }
1922
1923 Node* node() const
1924 {
1925 return edge().node();
1926 }
1927
1928#if USE(JSVALUE64)
1929 GPRReg gpr()
1930 {
1931 if (m_gprOrInvalid == InvalidGPRReg)
1932 m_gprOrInvalid = m_jit->fillJSValue(m_edge);
1933 return m_gprOrInvalid;
1934 }
1935 JSValueRegs jsValueRegs()
1936 {
1937 return JSValueRegs(gpr());
1938 }
1939#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
1940 bool isDouble() { return m_isDouble; }
1941
1942 void fill()
1943 {
1944 if (m_register.pair.tagGPR == InvalidGPRReg && m_register.pair.payloadGPR == InvalidGPRReg)
1945 m_isDouble = !m_jit->fillJSValue(m_edge, m_register.pair.tagGPR, m_register.pair.payloadGPR, m_register.fpr);
1946 }
1947
1948 GPRReg tagGPR()
1949 {
1950 fill();
1951 ASSERT(!m_isDouble);
1952 return m_register.pair.tagGPR;
1953 }
1954
1955 GPRReg payloadGPR()
1956 {
1957 fill();
1958 ASSERT(!m_isDouble);
1959 return m_register.pair.payloadGPR;
1960 }
1961
1962 JSValueRegs jsValueRegs()
1963 {
1964 return JSValueRegs(tagGPR(), payloadGPR());
1965 }
1966
1967 GPRReg gpr(WhichValueWord which)
1968 {
1969 return jsValueRegs().gpr(which);
1970 }
1971
1972 FPRReg fpr()
1973 {
1974 fill();
1975 ASSERT(m_isDouble);
1976 return m_register.fpr;
1977 }
1978#endif
1979
1980 void use()
1981 {
1982 m_jit->use(node());
1983 }
1984
1985private:
1986 SpeculativeJIT* m_jit;
1987 Edge m_edge;
1988#if USE(JSVALUE64)
1989 GPRReg m_gprOrInvalid;
1990#elif USE(JSVALUE32_64)
1991 union {
1992 struct {
1993 GPRReg tagGPR;
1994 GPRReg payloadGPR;
1995 } pair;
1996 FPRReg fpr;
1997 } m_register;
1998 bool m_isDouble;
1999#endif
2000};

2051// === Temporaries ===
2052//
2053// These classes are used to allocate temporary registers.
2054// A mechanism is provided to attempt to reuse the registers
2055// currently allocated to child nodes whose value is consumed
2056// by, and not live after, this operation.
2057
2058enum ReuseTag { Reuse };
2059
2060class GPRTemporary {
2061 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
2062public:
2063 GPRTemporary();
2064 GPRTemporary(SpeculativeJIT*);
2065 GPRTemporary(SpeculativeJIT*, GPRReg specific);
2066 template<typename T>
2067 GPRTemporary(SpeculativeJIT* jit, ReuseTag, T& operand)
2068 : m_jit(jit)
2069 , m_gpr(InvalidGPRReg)
2070 {
2071 if (m_jit->canReuse(operand.node()))
2072 m_gpr = m_jit->reuse(operand.gpr());
2073 else
2074 m_gpr = m_jit->allocate();
2075 }
2076 template<typename T1, typename T2>
2077 GPRTemporary(SpeculativeJIT* jit, ReuseTag, T1& op1, T2& op2)
2078 : m_jit(jit)
2079 , m_gpr(InvalidGPRReg)
2080 {
2081 if (m_jit->canReuse(op1.node()))
2082 m_gpr = m_jit->reuse(op1.gpr());
2083 else if (m_jit->canReuse(op2.node()))
2084 m_gpr = m_jit->reuse(op2.gpr());
2085 else if (m_jit->canReuse(op1.node(), op2.node()) && op1.gpr() == op2.gpr())
2086 m_gpr = m_jit->reuse(op1.gpr());
2087 else
2088 m_gpr = m_jit->allocate();
2089 }
2090 GPRTemporary(SpeculativeJIT*, ReuseTag, JSValueOperand&, WhichValueWord);
2091
2092 GPRTemporary(const GPRTemporary&) = delete;
2093
2094 GPRTemporary(GPRTemporary&& other)
2095 {
2096 ASSERT(other.m_jit);
2097 ASSERT(other.m_gpr != InvalidGPRReg);
2098 m_jit = other.m_jit;
2099 m_gpr = other.m_gpr;
2100 other.m_jit = nullptr;
2101 other.m_gpr = InvalidGPRReg;
2102 }
2103
2104 GPRTemporary& operator=(GPRTemporary&& other)
2105 {
2106 ASSERT(!m_jit);
2107 ASSERT(m_gpr == InvalidGPRReg);
2108 std::swap(m_jit, other.m_jit);
2109 std::swap(m_gpr, other.m_gpr);
2110 return *this;
2111 }
2112
2113 void adopt(GPRTemporary&);
2114
2115 ~GPRTemporary()
2116 {
2117 if (m_jit && m_gpr != InvalidGPRReg)
2118 m_jit->unlock(gpr());
2119 }
2120
2121 GPRReg gpr()
2122 {
2123 return m_gpr;
2124 }
2125
2126private:
2127 SpeculativeJIT* m_jit;
2128 GPRReg m_gpr;
2129};

2131class JSValueRegsTemporary {
2132 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
2133public:
2134 JSValueRegsTemporary();
2135 JSValueRegsTemporary(SpeculativeJIT*);
2136 template<typename T>
2137 JSValueRegsTemporary(SpeculativeJIT*, ReuseTag, T& operand, WhichValueWord resultRegWord = PayloadWord);
2138 JSValueRegsTemporary(SpeculativeJIT*, ReuseTag, JSValueOperand&);

2264// perform a speculative check for a more restrictive type than we can statically

2277#endif

2281 if (jit->isFilled(node()))
2282 gpr();
2283 }
2284
2285 ~SpeculateInt32Operand()

2288 m_jit->unlock(m_gprOrInvalid);

2292 {
2293 return m_edge;
2294 }
2295
2296 Node* node() const
2297 {
2298 return edge().node();
2299 }
2300
2301 DataFormat format()
2302 {
2303 gpr(); // m_format is set when m_gpr is locked.
2304 ASSERT(m_format == DataFormatInt32 || m_format == DataFormatJSInt32);
2305 return m_format;
2306 }
2307
2308 GPRReg gpr()
2309 {
2310 if (m_gprOrInvalid == InvalidGPRReg)
2311 m_gprOrInvalid = m_jit->fillSpeculateInt32(edge(), m_format);
2312 return m_gprOrInvalid;
2313 }
2314
2315 void use()
2316 {
2317 m_jit->use(node());
2318 }

2603 explicit SpeculateCellOperand(SpeculativeJIT* jit, Edge edge, OperandSpeculationMode mode = AutomaticOperandSpeculation)
2604 : m_jit(jit)
2605 , m_edge(edge)
2606 , m_gprOrInvalid(InvalidGPRReg)
2607 {
2608 ASSERT(m_jit);
2609 if (!edge)
2610 return;
2611 ASSERT_UNUSED(mode, mode == ManualOperandSpeculation || isCell(edge.useKind()));
2612 if (jit->isFilled(node()))
2613 gpr();
2614 }
2615
2616 explicit SpeculateCellOperand(SpeculateCellOperand&& other)
2617 {
2618 m_jit = other.m_jit;
2619 m_edge = other.m_edge;
2620 m_gprOrInvalid = other.m_gprOrInvalid;
2621
2622 other.m_gprOrInvalid = InvalidGPRReg;
2623 other.m_edge = Edge();
2624 }
2625
2626 ~SpeculateCellOperand()
2627 {
2628 if (!m_edge)
2629 return;
2630 ASSERT(m_gprOrInvalid != InvalidGPRReg);
2631 m_jit->unlock(m_gprOrInvalid);
2632 }
2633
2634 Edge edge() const
2635 {
2636 return m_edge;
2637 }
2638
2639 Node* node() const
2640 {
2641 return edge().node();
2642 }
2643
2644 GPRReg gpr()
2645 {
2646 ASSERT(m_edge);
2647 if (m_gprOrInvalid == InvalidGPRReg)
2648 m_gprOrInvalid = m_jit->fillSpeculateCell(edge());
2649 return m_gprOrInvalid;
2650 }
2651
2652 void use()
2653 {
2654 ASSERT(m_edge);
2655 m_jit->use(node());
2656 }
2657
2658private:
2659 SpeculativeJIT* m_jit;
2660 Edge m_edge;
2661 GPRReg m_gprOrInvalid;
2662};

2762#define DFG_TYPE_CHECK_WITH_EXIT_KIND(exitKind, source, edge, typesPassedThrough, jumpToFail) do { \
2763 JSValueSource _dtc_source = (source); \
2764 Edge _dtc_edge = (edge); \
2765 SpeculatedType _dtc_typesPassedThrough = typesPassedThrough; \
2766 if (!needsTypeCheck(_dtc_edge, _dtc_typesPassedThrough)) \
2767 break; \
2768 typeCheck(_dtc_source, _dtc_edge, _dtc_typesPassedThrough, (jumpToFail), exitKind); \
2769 } while (0)

2772 DFG_TYPE_CHECK_WITH_EXIT_KIND(BadType, source, edge, typesPassedThrough, jumpToFail)
